
Switch statements can be used as a substitute for long if...else...if ladders.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[switch Statement]
switch (variable/expression) {
case value1:
   // statements of case1
   break;

case value2:
   // statements of case2
   break;

   .. .. ...
   .. .. ...

default:
   // default statements
}evaluates the expression (mostly variable) and compares it with values (can be expressions) of each case label
if the value matches a certain case label, then all the statements of the matching case label are executed

-only works with:

Java Primitive data types: byte, short, char, and int
Java Enumerated types
Java String Class
Java Wrapper Classes: Character, Byte, Short, and Integer.
